<a name="0">[0]</a> <a href="#0" id=0>There is a convergence of file systems, database systems, and programming languages.</a>
<a name="1">[1]</a> <a href="#1" id=1>Extensible database systems use object-oriented techniques from programming languages to allow you to define complex objects as native database types.</a>
<a name="2">[2]</a> <a href="#2" id=2>It seems very likely that these nascent database systems will be integrated with the main-line database systems in the next decade or that some new species of metadata driven analysis and workflow system will supplant both traditional databases and the science-specific file formats and their tool suites.</a>
